Comments: \u00a77\u00a7oThe article is already available on the servermath.AG/9904088. Its main purpose is to compute a determinant formula for the determinant of Gau\u00df-Manin cohomology of a rank one irregular connection on a family of

curves. In the original version, we computed modulo torsion. To please the referee, we computed here the torsion as well. It is a 2-torsion term. We give for it two shapes. One version is to express it as the residue of some quadratic
form stemming from the connection on the curve, and one as the discriminant of some Hessian on the generalized Picard variety. 51 pages\u00a7r
